304 #if defined ( __CC_ARM )
305 /* ARM Compiler
306  ------------
307  RAM functions are defined using the toolchain options.
308  Functions that are executed in RAM should reside in a separate source module.
309  Using the 'Options for File' dialog you can simply change the 'Code / Const'
310  area of a module to a memory space in physical RAM.
311  Available memory areas are declared in the 'Target' tab of the 'Options for Target'
312  dialog.
313 */
314  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status
315 
316 #elif defined ( __ICCARM__ )
317 /* ICCARM Compiler
318  ---------------
319  RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain keyword "__ramfunc".
320 */
321  #define __RAM_FUNC __ramfunc FLASH_Status
322 
323 #elif defined ( __GNUC__ )
324 /* GNU Compiler
325  ------------
326  RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain attribute
327  "__attribute__((section(".RamFunc")))".
328 */
329  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status __attribute__((section(".RamFunc")))
330 
331 #elif defined ( __TASKING__ )
332 /* TASKING Compiler
333  ----------------
334  RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain pragma. This pragma is
335  defined in the stm32l1xx_flash_ramfunc.c
336 */
337  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status
338 
339 #endif
